abbr: Master Boot Record


The MBR is the first sector on → hardware/harddisk/index. Its size is 512 bytes of which 446 is a small piece of code and the remaining 64 bytes are the → hardware/harddisk/partition-table that describe
the → hardware/harddisk/partition[partitions] on the harddisk.


{ Limitations {

  Partition size limit of 2TiB.

}
{ See also {

  → Linux/booting/GRUB, → hardware/harddisk/GPT

}
